with mold, and well...

148
00:09:57,463 --> 00:09:58,623
How embarrassing!

149
00:09:59,065 --> 00:10:00,862
Why are you upset and making
excuses like that?

150
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:03,202
Idiot! What are you doing?

151
00:10:03,202 --> 00:10:04,804
Hurry up and put on some clothes.

152
00:10:04,804 --> 00:10:08,574
Oh, what's wrong with you Ryo?
Since when you are shy like that?

153
00:10:08,574 --> 00:10:10,201
No! If you don't do anything now...

154
00:10:10,710 --> 00:10:12,678
Mary, breakfast is ready...

155
00:10:13,579 --> 00:10:15,781
You jerk, first thing in the morning, you're...

156
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:18,750
What the hell are you doing!?

157
00:10:22,021 --> 00:10:23,756
Wow, poor baby.

158
00:10:23,756 --> 00:10:25,417
No breakfast for you!

159
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:30,563
Something is wrong with you. You could
have escaped from her attack.

160
00:10:30,563 --> 00:10:32,121
Shut up! It's all your fault!

161
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:34,900
What kind of relationship is there
between you and her?

162
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:37,528
It seemed like she was jealous
of me, didn't it?

163
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,930
She just has violence syndrome.

164
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,708
I got it! Let's make the story short.

165
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:45,711
You don't want her to know about
your past because you love her.

166
00:10:45,711 --> 00:10:48,481
If she finds out all about your past,
she might leave you!

167
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,249
What kind of misunderstanding is that?

168
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:52,118
Other than that, is there any
other good reason

169
00:10:52,118 --> 00:10:53,819
why you keep an amateur like her
as your assistant?

170
00:10:53,819 --> 00:10:56,522
She doesn't have any relatives or
family, so I let her stay here.

171
00:10:56,522 --> 00:10:58,758
She's a mature woman.

172
00:10:58,758 --> 00:11:02,216
You don't need to take care of her,
not like me at that time.

173
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:07,463
Don't you think this is a good opportunity
for you to make her get out of this world?

174
00:11:09,902 --> 00:11:14,930
Screw her! She knows Ryo a little bit better
than I do, and she acts like she is so big.

175
00:11:21,881 --> 00:11:24,817
I'm indeed an amateur...

176
00:11:24,817 --> 00:11:26,580
Shall I be your coach?

177
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:30,315
No thanks.

178
00:11:33,426 --> 00:11:37,163
Can you go out with me and
give me a guided tour now?

179
00:11:37,163 --> 00:11:40,826
Why me? I thought you would
ask Ryo to do that.

180
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:45,303
You have something to ask me, don't you?

181
00:12:08,828 --> 00:12:11,163
Well...

182
00:12:11,163 --> 00:12:15,566
You want to ask me why Ryo doesn't
know his birthday, don't you?

183
00:12:17,069 --> 00:12:18,304
You really want to know that badly?

184
00:12:18,304 --> 00:12:20,072
I can't stop thinking about it.

185
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:22,108
What shall I do?

186
00:12:22,108 --> 00:12:24,176
Ryo told me not to tell anything to you.

187
00:12:24,176 --> 00:12:28,414
However, if you are going to marry Ryo,
I think you should know.

188
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:30,416
Marry?!

189
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:35,087
But I'm his assistant now

190
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:38,454
and I think I should know the same facts
that his former assistant knew.

191
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:46,098
I don't mind telling you about it,
but after you find out,

192
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:51,400
you might think that you and him
don't belong in the same world.

193
00:12:52,505 --> 00:12:57,676
You might start thinking that you can't be
with him and you might leave him.

194
00:12:57,676 --> 00:12:59,644
Do you still want to know?

195
00:13:01,247 --> 00:13:02,271
Yes...

196
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:06,277
I see, okay.

197
00:13:08,921 --> 00:13:10,156
This glass is not clean enough.

198
00:13:10,156 --> 00:13:12,124
Oh, this menu has some stains!

199
00:13:12,491 --> 00:13:14,459
Let's go. This place is no good.

200
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:23,302
Missed it.

201
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:24,963
Miki, please excuse me.

202
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:29,508
None of our business.

203
00:13:29,508 --> 00:13:31,644
Ah, I want to know!

204
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:35,948
Falcon, don't you want to know,
or do you already know?

205
00:13:35,948 --> 00:13:37,745
If you already know, can you tell us?!

206
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:43,684
Oh, we understand. We won't say
anything anymore. Yes, Sir!

207
00:13:56,569 --> 00:13:59,367
The place where he was raised,
it was not in Japan.

208
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:03,075
Oh, so surprised?

209
00:14:03,075 --> 00:14:06,612
Did you think an extraordinary man like him
had been raised in Japan normally,

210
00:14:06,612 --> 00:14:09,046
and went to school here?

211
00:14:09,415 --> 00:14:11,283
Well...

212
00:14:11,283 --> 00:14:15,621
He was raised in a place which is very far
from the life of ordinary Japanese,

213
00:14:15,621 --> 00:14:19,250
surrounded by lots of blood and
uncountable dead bodies.

214
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:22,718
That place was the battlefield.

215
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,489
The battlefield?!

216
00:14:43,949 --> 00:14:49,080
When he was a little kid, he was already
carrying guns in the middle of the battlefield.

217
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:53,225
In a small country in Central America,
which had been in a civil war for a long time.

218
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:56,228
Central America? Why was he there?

219
00:14:56,228 --> 00:14:57,963
He is Japanese, isn't he?

220
00:14:57,963 --> 00:15:00,466
Of course, he's pure Japanese.

221
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:04,596
When he was little, he was thrown into the
middle of the jungle by himself, all alone.

222
00:15:05,271 --> 00:15:07,239
There was a plane crash.

223
00:15:16,982 --> 00:15:23,444
Either sightseeing or for business, anyway,
he was in that place with his parents.

224
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:30,962
Then, the plane crashed.

225
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:46,872
He lost his parents there. He appeared
to be the only survivor of that crash.

226
00:15:47,546 --> 00:15:51,573
He wandered in the jungle for days,
and finally arrived at a village.

227
00:15:53,185 --> 00:15:58,646
A village of guerrillas, which had been
fighting against government forces.

228
00:15:59,425 --> 00:16:02,127
Their village needed only warriors.

229
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:04,229
In order to live in the village,

230
00:16:04,229 --> 00:16:07,255
he didn't have any choice but
to become a guerrilla warrior.

231
00:16:07,866 --> 00:16:13,272
He was a little kid, who didn't even know
his full name, nor his birthday,

232
00:16:13,272 --> 00:16:18,266
but in order to survive, he had to learn
how to fight and live while fighting.

233
00:16:19,011 --> 00:16:22,208
On top of that, he didn't have anybody
he could rely on.

234
00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:27,675
Everybody there fought without thinking
about anything but surviving day by day.

235
00:16:28,587 --> 00:16:33,125
Days passed, years passed, but the war
never ends in that country.

236
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:35,494
In the war, it seemed like it lasted forever.

237
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:38,930
People lost time, lost track of dates
and their own age.

238
00:16:45,738 --> 00:16:50,368
The war finally ended with the victory by the
governmental forces after a long, long time.

239
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:56,749
Ryo and the other anti-government guerrillas
were chased out, scattering from the country.

240
00:16:56,749 --> 00:17:00,119
Ryo and one of the guerrillas went to the US

241
00:17:00,119 --> 00:17:03,088
and they joined the underground
world as a pair.

242
00:17:04,556 --> 00:17:10,188
His partner died shortly, and after him,
I took over the position of Ryo's partner.

243
00:17:11,663 --> 00:17:16,802
Now, you understand the reason why Ryo
doesn't know his birthday, don't you?

244
00:17:16,802 --> 00:17:18,997
How do you feel? Are you satisfied?

245
00:17:21,273 --> 00:17:24,109
She was shocked, just as I thought.

246
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:27,946
But you are the one who wanted to hear.

247
00:17:27,946 --> 00:17:31,074
You are not the kind of woman who
can be with a man like Ryo.

248
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:35,512
It'd be best for you to leave him now.

249
00:17:52,304 --> 00:17:54,673
My shoulder has been dislocated!

250
00:17:54,673 --> 00:17:56,175
Hey, wait a sec, babe!

251
00:17:56,175 --> 00:17:58,644
You hurt my brother and leave
without doing anything?

252
00:17:58,644 --> 00:18:01,613
Why don't you pay us for treatment?!

253
00:18:06,485 --> 00:18:08,112
I am so sorry!

254
00:18:10,289 --> 00:18:11,449
Umibozu...

255
00:18:14,159 --> 00:18:17,930
He's mean! He went out without us!

256
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:21,100
I know he probably followed Kaori!

257
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:25,366
He acted like that, but he must have been
interested in Saeba's past!

258
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:28,402
Oh, Saeba.

259
00:18:29,041 --> 00:18:31,310
What's wrong? He doesn't look so good.

260
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:35,269
I think he didn't want Kaori
to know about his past.

261
00:18:37,716 --> 00:18:43,313
That's why he looks sad. He thinks
that Kaori might leave him.

262
00:18:44,256 --> 00:18:46,724
Hi, nice to see you again.

263
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:53,365
I told her everything. She was very
shocked by the story, I guess.

264
00:18:53,365 --> 00:18:56,101
She might not come back to you ever again.

265
00:18:56,101 --> 00:18:57,936
But this is good.

266
00:18:57,936 --> 00:19:02,066
A woman like her shouldn't have anything
to do with the underground world.

267
00:19:03,442 --> 00:19:04,739
What?!

268
00:19:05,043 --> 00:19:05,878
Saeba!

269
00:19:05,878 --> 00:19:06,742
Calm down!

270
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,448
I found it!

271
00:19:10,883 --> 00:19:12,985
Hey, you, mokkori beauty!

272
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:15,621
Hey, let's go out together!

273
00:19:15,621 --> 00:19:19,921
I asked thirty girls, but every one of them
said no, so I'm depressed!

274
00:19:22,628 --> 00:19:24,596
Go away I said!

275
00:19:27,065 --> 00:19:29,835
The thirty-first girl has just denied my offer.

276
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:32,133
I'm more and more depressed.

277
00:19:32,437 --> 00:19:35,574
I was worried about him,
but he's the same as always.

278
00:19:35,574 --> 00:19:37,565
I can't believe him!

279
00:19:40,279 --> 00:19:43,315
I guess you are pretty shocked, aren't you?

280
00:19:43,315 --> 00:19:45,083
Yes...

281
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:48,253
I can't believe that Ryo has
a horrible past like that.

282
00:19:48,253 --> 00:19:51,590
I feel as if he's suddenly so far from me.

283
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:54,491
But that's not the only reason
I feel so depressed.

284
00:19:55,928 --> 00:20:01,066
While I was listening to Mary,
I felt miserable.

285
00:20:01,066 --> 00:20:04,433
Because I didn't know anything
about Ryo's past.

286
00:20:05,404 --> 00:20:11,410
The reason she knows about it, is because
Ryo told her about him, isn't it?

287
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:13,612
However, even though I have been
with him for over three years,

288
00:20:13,612 --> 00:20:14,947
he has never told me anything.

289
00:20:14,947 --> 00:20:17,916
Why? Why doesn't he trust me?

290
00:20:18,684 --> 00:20:22,988
For Ryo, my existence is nothing like that.

291
00:20:22,988 --> 00:20:27,192
Ryo doesn't trust me as his assistant.

292
00:20:27,192 --> 00:20:31,151
I'm jealous of her and feel miserable,
and I hate doing so.

293
00:20:33,799 --> 00:20:36,597
Really I feel miserable.

294
00:20:39,271 --> 00:20:44,937
Ryo might have been afraid of the possibility
that you might see him in a different way.

295
00:20:47,145 --> 00:20:51,850
He might have tried to avoid breaking
the relationship between you and him.

296
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:55,809
He doesn't consider you just a partner.

297
00:20:57,389 --> 00:21:01,723
He looks at you as more than just a partner.

298
00:21:02,394 --> 00:21:06,194
More than a partner? What do you mean?

299
00:21:06,865 --> 00:21:08,332
It means...

300
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:13,735
I can't say something embarrassing
like that in my own words.

301
00:21:14,873 --> 00:21:15,999
Umibozu!

302
00:21:17,876 --> 00:21:21,246
Let me tell you one more thing.

303
00:21:21,246 --> 00:21:24,409
Ryo didn't tell Mary about his past.

304
00:21:25,517 --> 00:21:28,487
The man who was Ryo's first partner,

305
00:21:28,487 --> 00:21:32,557
the one who was a guerrilla and
went to the US with Ryo...

306
00:21:32,557 --> 00:21:36,891
He taught Ryo everything about
how to fight and trained him.

307
00:21:39,164 --> 00:21:41,359
He was also Mary's father.

308
00:21:43,602 --> 00:21:47,105
Then Mary heard the story from her father.

309
00:21:47,105 --> 00:21:51,410
That's right. He's never told
anyone about himself.

310
00:21:51,410 --> 00:21:59,146
Now, you think about what
to do for yourself.

311
00:22:00,085 --> 00:22:02,110
Thank you, Umibozu.

312
00:22:12,798 --> 00:22:16,735
I wanted you to listen to my guitar

313
00:22:16,735 --> 00:22:20,432
I wanted to convey my feelings
about you to you

314
00:22:20,872 --> 00:22:26,333
But I couldn't do so

315
00:22:29,381 --> 00:22:36,844
You don't know anything about
this town where I live

316
00:22:37,289 --> 00:22:43,250
You don't know the reason I'm here

317
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:58,176
If that moment could have colored
the rows of old brick houses

318
00:22:58,176 --> 00:23:01,543
I wouldn't have let you go

319
00:23:02,013 --> 00:23:09,818
When I cross the park shining
in the winter sun

320
00:23:10,155 --> 00:23:16,060
Everyday life is starting

321
00:23:18,463 --> 00:23:26,336
In my mind, time has stopped

322
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:32,677
And a double-decker bus is passing

323
00:23:38,917 --> 00:23:41,153
It's a good thing that you take Mary out
and guide her around,

324
00:23:41,153 --> 00:23:43,555
but it's too obvious what you're really
thinking. Your face is relaxed.

325
00:23:43,555 --> 00:23:46,558
There are so many obstacles and
my date is destroyed.

326
00:23:46,558 --> 00:23:49,995
I thought something was wrong, but I
didn't know Mary was trying to kill me.

327
00:23:49,995 --> 00:23:51,863
You were so happy when she asked you
to go to the hotel together,

328
00:23:51,863 --> 00:23:52,798
but somebody shot you?

329
00:23:52,798 --> 00:23:53,298
Damn it!
And somebody shot you?

330
00:23:53,298 --> 00:23:53,799
Damn it!

331
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:57,235
But why? Why does she want to kill you,
her former partner?!

332
00:23:57,235 --> 00:23:58,503
City Hunter 2:

333
00:23:58,503 --> 00:24:02,174
"Good Luck, My Sweeper
City Streets for Both of Us (Part 2)"

334
00:24:02,174 --> 00:24:04,142
If you miss it, someone will try to kill you!

335
00:24:04,643 --> 00:24:08,272
Please look forward to the next episode

